ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend this course. It was a lot of fun and I think I learned a lot. David was a great teacher.
I would summarize the class as a class in which you learn how to operate fundamental machines, and learn necessary techniques to be able to design, cut, and shape metal.
This is an excellent class. Definitely take it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It was nice to get some real hands on experience and learn how the basics of machining. I think it has the potential to be very useful in my research.

As an electrical engineer my understanding of machining was virtually nil. However during this course I learned how to operate machines safely. It has certainly helped with my research as I can design and build components for my projects by myself now.
